cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper studies the power-performance relationship of power-efficient computing, which is related to performance optimization. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper investigates the interplay of system operations including server farm size, which suggests a distributed computing perspective. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper analyzes system on/off decisions and threshold mechanisms, which are related to control theory. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses processing speed optimization, which is related to hardware architecture. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Although not the main focus, the paper mentions job batching, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
